data.description:
In Spanish, sentences not only end with exclamation and question marks, but also begin with them (actually flipped over version).

It looks like:

```
¿Cómo estás?      -> How are you?
¡Es maravilloso!  -> It is wonderful!
¡¿Qué haces?!     -> What are you doing?!
¿¡Donde esta!?    -> Where is it!?
```
You have an unput ```array``` with exclamatory or interrogative sentences inside. Your task is to check each each of tnem for "Spanish way", to convert them if they are not and to return new array with "spanish" elements in the same order as in the original array.

For example:

```
input:  ['Are you fine?', 'Why not?!', 'So what!?', 'It is you!']);
output: ['¿Are you fine?', '¡¿Why not?!', '¿¡So what!?', '¡It is you!'];

input:  ['Are? you? fine????', 'Why no!!?t?!', 'So! what!?', 'It is you!!!']);
output: ['¿Are? you? fine????', '¡¿Why no!!?t?!', '¿¡So! what!?!?', '¡It is you!!!'];

input:  ['¿Are you fine?', '¡¿Why not?!', '¿¡So!!! what!?', '¡It is!?! you!']);
output: ['¿Are you fine?', '¡¿Why not?!', '¿¡So!!! what!?', '¡It is!?! you!'];

```
P.S. Array's length > 0. 
For clarity, sentences ending with ```!?``` consider as a ```!?``` and ```!??``` consider as a ```?```
